target.message: Added shutdown function to remote stage's worker process, as it was missing
Include wait timeouts in calculation of maximum shot duration.
Bumped major version number and close gated-clocks branch
Added nicer view of the SLM
Fixed bugs in NewPortMirrorController. A basic script now compiles.

Close pulseblaster_asymmetric_pulses branch - it has been merged in via
its descendants novatech_async_updates and Generic Attributes
Fix incorrect deprecated import alias for dummy pseudoclock

Fixed bug in NI_PCIe_6363 where acquisitions after a wait did not account for the wait time.
This addresses issue #19.

Added support for configurable voltage range on NI analog inputs.

A new AnalogIn class has been created in NIBoard.py called NIAnalogIn. The signature of this class is backwards compatible with AnalogIn, and the defaults for the new keyword arguments (min/max) match those hard coded into the existing NI BLACS classes.
The NI classes with analog inputs have been updated to use the min/max values specified in the device properties of the NI card.

All changes are backwards compatible with the previous API and should maintain the original behaviour if no modifications are made to the labscript file.
